{"lemma":"عَنَتِ","slug":"عَنَتِ","root":"ع.ن.ت","root_slug":"ع-ن-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ن-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَنَتِ","root":"عنو","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30697","n30702","n30703"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30697","headword_ar":"عَنِتَ","root":"Ent","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanatN","text_ar":"عَنَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fell into a difficult, hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressing, case:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanatN","text_ar":"عَنَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meeting with difficulty, hardship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [This is held by some to be the primary signification: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanato","text_ar":"عَنَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below; by the explanations of which it seems to be indicated that the verb has several significations that are not expressly assigned to it in the lexicons.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaziyzN Ealayohi maA Eanit~umo","text_ar":"عَزِيزٌ عَلَيْهِ مَا عَنِتُّمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [ix. last verse but one], means, accord. to Az [and most of the expositors],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grievous unto him is your experiencing difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, the meaning is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aEonatakumo","text_ar":"مَا اَعْنَتَكُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what hath brought you into difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [In the S and O, it seems to be indicated by the context that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Eanit~umo","text_ar":"مَا عَنِتُّمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"your having sinned."},{"kind":"text","text":"]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanitati Ald~aAb~apu","text_ar":"عَنِتَتِ الدَّابَّةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beast limped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"halted, in consequence of hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough, treatment, such as it could not bear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoEala daAb~atahu faEanitato","text_ar":"اَنْعَلَ دَابَّتَهُ فَعَنِتَتْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He shod his beast and it became lame:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus as some relate it; as others relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEatabato","text_ar":"فَعَتَبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the former relation is preferred by Kt. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanita","text_ar":"عَنِتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a bone, (Az, A, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanitato","text_ar":"عَنِتَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of an arm or a leg, (Az, TA,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanatN","text_ar":"عَنَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It broke"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, A, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after its having been set and united:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) [this is said in the Ksh and by Bd, in iv. 30, to be the primary signification:] and the former, said of a bone,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became weak, and broke."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanita","text_ar":"عَنِتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanatN","text_ar":"عَنَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * O, * Msb, K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He committed a sin, a crime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an act of disobedience deserving punishment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, * TA: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he committed sins, crimes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acts of disobedience deserving punishment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did wrong"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intentionally"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unintentionally"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) [And particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He committed fornication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adultery:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanatN","text_ar":"عَنَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.]"}],"source_refs":["Az","A","K","TA","S","O","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n30702","headword_ar":"عَنَتٌ","root":"Ent","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of 1, q. v.: and also expl. as having the following meanings:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Difficulty, hardship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, IAth, Mgh, Msb, TA:) this is [said to be] the primary signification: (Jel in iv. 30:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2169},{"kind":"text","text":"TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming of difficulty"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon a man. (K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of perdition"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destruction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, IAth, K, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bad, an evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a corrupt, state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad, evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fasaAdN","text_ar":"فَسَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which has both of these meanings; and may here have the former meaning as nearly agreeing with what precedes it, or the latter meaning as nearly agreeing with what follows it]. (A, IAth, K, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sin, a crime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an act of disobedience deserving punishment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, S, A, IAth, O, K, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonatapN","text_ar":"مَعْنَتَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wrong action"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intentional"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unintentional"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an error; mistake."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Msb, * TA.) ―         -b6-  ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fornication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adultery:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, IAth, Mgh, O, Msb, K, TA:) but this is a conventional explanation of the lecturers of the colleges. (Mgh.) So in the Kur [iv. 30], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika limano xa$iYa A@loEanata minokumo","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ لِمَنْ خَشِىَ ا@لْعَنَتَ مِنْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is for him, among you, who fears the commission of fornication"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O, Msb, TA: [and the like is said in the Mgh:]) this, says Az, was revealed in relation to him who might not have the means of taking to wife a free woman; therefore it was allowed to him to take to wife a slave: (Msb, TA:) or the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEnt","text_ar":"العنت"},{"kind":"text","text":"here is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perdition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perdition in"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fornication."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wrongful, unjust, injurious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannical, conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"annoyance, molestation, harm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hurt."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Distressing, grievous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afflicting, harm, injury, hurt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  And accord. to the 'Ináyeh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Contention;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contention for superiority in greatness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persistence in opposition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in vain contention."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","IAth","Mgh","Msb","TA","S","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n30703","headword_ar":"عَنِتٌ","root":"Ent","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A bone"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken after its having been set and united;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEonatN","text_ar":"مُعْنَتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}